file.name: why_do_you_want_to_work_for_pusher.txt
file.title: why do you want to work for pusher
file.preview:
Why do you want to work for Pusher?

Three reasons: realtime is interesting as it is part of most of the current trends. There seems to be a gold rush towards the on-demand, give-me-stuff-this-moment economy. Pusher supports that gold rush by selling pick axes and shovels in the form of the infrastructure that powers that. Plenty of room to grow here.
I've been building consumer products for a long time, but I also really enjoyed any opportunity to build tools for other developers. I'd like to focus more on that kind of work.
I'm passionate about supporting developers and developer communities. Either through talks, blogposts, trainings or sample apps - it's a great feeling and I'd love to become better at it. You employ people in developer relations. It would allow me to learn from professionals.
file.preview_highlight:
Why do you want to work for Pusher?


Three reasons: realtime is interesting as it is part of most of the current trends. There seems to be a gold rush towards the on-demand, give-me-stuff-this-moment economy. Pusher supports that gold rush by selling pick axes and shovels in the form of the infrastructure that powers that. Plenty of room to grow here.


I've been building consumer products for a long time, but I also really enjoyed any opportunity to build tools for other developers. I'd like to focus more on that kind of work.


I'm passionate about supporting developers and developer communities. Either through talks, blogposts, trainings or sample apps - it's a great feeling and I'd love to become better at it. You employ people in developer relations. It would allow me to learn from professionals.
